com.google.appinventor.components.scripts

Class ComponentProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • com.google.appinventor.components.scripts.ComponentProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.annotation.processing.Processor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ComponentDescriptorGenerator, ComponentListGenerator, ComponentTranslationGenerator, DocumentationGenerator, LangDefXmlGenerator

    public abstract class ComponentProcessor
extends javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
    Processor for generating output files based on the annotations and javadoc in the component source code.

    Specifically, this reads over the source files, building up a representation of components and their designer properties, properties, methods, and events. Concrete subclasses implement the method outputResults() to generate output.

    Currently, the following annotations are used:

    • DesignerComponent and SimpleObject to identify components. Subclasses can distinguish between the two through the boolean fields ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo.designerComponent and ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo.simpleObject.
    • DesignerProperty to identify designer properties.
    • SimpleProperty to identify properties.
    • SimpleFunction to identify methods.
    • SimpleEvent to identify events.
    Author:
    spertus@google.com (Ellen Spertus) [lyn, 2015/12/29] Added deprecated instance variable to ParameterizedFeature. This is inherited by Event, Method, and Property, which are modified slightly to handle it.

      • components

        protected final java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.String,ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo> components
        Information about every App Inventor component. Keys are fully-qualified names (such as "com.google.appinventor.components.runtime.components.android.Label"), and values are the corresponding ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo objects. This is constructed by process(java.util.Set<? extends javax.lang.model.element.TypeElement>, javax.annotation.processing.RoundEnvironment) for use in outputResults().

      • outputResults

        protected abstract void outputResults()
                               throws java.io.IOException

        Outputs the required component information in the desired format. It is called by process(java.util.Set<? extends javax.lang.model.element.TypeElement>, javax.annotation.processing.RoundEnvironment) after the fields components and messager have been populated.

        Implementations of this methods should call getOutputWriter(String) to obtain a Writer for their output. Diagnostic messages should be written using messager.

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • javaTypeToYailType

        Returns the appropriate Yail type (e.g., "number" or "text") for a given Java type (e.g., "float" or "java.lang.String"). All component names are converted to "component".
        Parameters:

        Returns:
